&lt;p&gt;Smartly.io is currently looking for a Chief of Staff to join our growing team!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Chief of Staff to the Chief Product Officer (CPO) is a senior, highly trusted partner who amplifies the effectiveness of the Product organization and its leader. This role blends strategy, analytics, and execution, acting as an extension of the CPO across planning, decision-making, and cross-functional alignment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not an administrative role. It is a thought partner and operator role designed for someone with top-tier strategic rigor, deep analytical skills, and experience driving complex initiatives inside high-growth or Big Tech environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will help turn product vision into reality by shaping strategy, driving operating cadence, surfacing insights, and ensuring the Product org delivers measurable customer and business impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Thought Partnership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a primary strategic advisor to the CPO on product vision, portfolio tradeoffs, org design, and long-term bets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead structured problem solving on ambiguous, high-stakes questions (e.g. build vs. buy, sequencing of AI investments, platform vs. feature tradeoffs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare clear, data-backed narratives for the CEO, executive team, and Board&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operating Rhythm &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the Product organization’s operating cadence: planning cycles, roadmap reviews, KPI reviews, and executive updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and unblock critical cross-team initiatives spanning Product Management, Design, Engineering, Product Marketing, and AI Platform teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure alignment between product strategy, commercial priorities, and go-to-market execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-Functional Leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a connective layer between Product and key partners including Engineering, Sales, Marketing, Customer Success, and Finance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead or support high-impact, cross-functional programs (e.g. major platform launches, AI initiatives, org transformations)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and proactively resolve misalignment before it becomes execution risk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication &amp;amp; Narrative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Craft concise, compelling written and visual materials for exec forums, Board meetings, and customer-facing moments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pressure-test messaging to ensure product strategy is clear, credible, and grounded in customer value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Raise the bar on clarity, precision, and decision quality across Product leadership communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ah Hoc Product &amp;amp; Business Analytics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own deep-dive analysis to inform new initiatives or key decisions (prioritization, investments, and KPI tracking)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draw customer and business insights from product usage, adoption, retention, monetization, and roadmap performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain core dashboards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel with CPO when needed to provide on-the-ground support for important events and team activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for you if you have...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8–12+ years of experience across a combination of:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Top-tier management consulting (e.g. McKinsey, BCG, Bain or equivalent)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product strategy, business operations, or strategy &amp;amp; operations roles at a high-growth or Big Tech company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience working closely with senior executives and influencing at the C-level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience operating in complex, platform-based SaaS or technology businesses strongly preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical &amp;amp; Technical Skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced proficiency in SQL and strong working knowledge of Python for analysis and modeling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort working directly with large datasets, dashboards, and experimentation results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to move seamlessly between quantitative analysis, qualitative research and strategic synthesis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership &amp;amp; Mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional structured thinking and problem-solving ability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High judgment, discretion, and ability to operate in ambiguity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong executive presence with the ability to challenge constructively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bias toward action, clarity, and impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer You...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Five weeks paid time off (PTO), 11 company paid holidays, unlimited sick days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous healthcare packages &amp;amp; mental health benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401K plus matching &amp;amp; equity grants for all new Smartlies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wellness benefit &amp;amp; learning reimbursement opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Volunteer time off days &amp;amp; company donation matching opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And so much more…&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Smartly is committed to being the best place to work for growth-minded individuals to thrive - explore more in our&lt;a href=&quot;https://assets.website-files.com/63d671dfba7daa79b745ce98/658068a97117b92f5dde8b02_Culture%20Handbook_181223.pdf&quot;&gt; Culture Handbook&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The base pay range for this position is as mentioned below per year, plus an annual performance bonus. We take into consideration an individual’s background, expertise, and experience in determining final salary. In addition to annual salary, Smartly’s total rewards provide employees with stock options, medical/dental/vision insurances, retirement savings benefits, parental leave, 5 weeks vacation, unlimited sick days, life insurance, and disability benefits. This information is provided in accordance with applicable law. Base pay information is based on market location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary Range (USD):&lt;/strong&gt; $140,000 – $190,000&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Smartly&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Smartly is the AI-powered advertising technology company transforming ad experiences for brands and their consumers. Our comprehensive advertising platform seamlessly integrates the capabilities of media, creative, and intelligence to power more than 800 billion impressions and generate more than 300 billion creatives annually, delivering tangible business outcomes for brands and advertisers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Smartly is the only company in the industry recognized as a Leader in The Forrester Wave: Creative Advertising Technologies with PwC validating the results it delivers for brands. We manage creative and media for 700+ brands worldwide and $6B in ad spend across the largest media platforms, including Facebook, Google, Instagram, Pinterest, Snap, and TikTok. Our end-to-end technology, unmatched access to media platforms and exceptional customer service help Fortune 500 brands to reach and engage consumers and learn what performs best.Smartly is a multinational and diverse team of 750+ Smartlies from 60+ nationalities, working in 13 countries. Together, we want to create and maintain an inclusive environment where everyone feels respected and heard. Our Diversity, Equity &amp;amp; Inclusion approach is at the heart of it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Visit &lt;a class=&quot;c-link c-link--underline&quot; href=&quot;http://smartly.io/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;http://Smartly.io&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;Smartly&lt;/a&gt; to learn more.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The processing of your information is described in our &lt;a href=&quot;https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/67ed4ab7f914accf87aa070c/698a11cb716926c1d76c1641_Smartly.io%20Group%20-%20Privacy%20Notice%20for%20Candidates%20-%201_2026.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Candidate Privacy Notice&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to Head of Americas Platform Sales, the Technical Advisor will play a key role in driving AMER Sales’ most critical initiatives with efficiency and speed. You will contribute to projects and programs that shape the future of AMER Sales at Stripe. With the ability to influence from a strategic and administrative perspective, you will be instrumental in executing key cross-org initiatives and helping us move from strategy to execution while ensuring operational excellence.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are energized by new user acquisition, go to market strategy, driving revenue generation, building relationships with executive stakeholders, and engaging with cross functional teams to drive and iterate Stripe’s strategy, then we want to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with kicking off, fixing, and or taking on time sensitive projects and programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend planning and review meetings with, or in lieu of the leader&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and orchestrate processes and communications across multiple sales teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interface and consult regularly with internal cross-functional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate background for meetings with key partners (e.g., identify goals and talking points, provide background on attendees, analyze the current business relationship, etc.) and ensure prep is ready&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive insights and efficiencies in how we execute to achieve our goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up to date on changes and trends related to the business across GTM and Product&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a network of internal and external resources to expedite deal management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great collaboration and people skills. You will need to build relationships with leaders, stakeholders and cross functional partners across the broader organization to drive impact at scale. It will be important that you are able to delegate and influence rather than try to take everything on yourself.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Superior verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High org EQ to get to decision makers quickly and engage effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidence to navigate complex problems without clear guidance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to make sound judgment calls in unstructured situations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to quickly assimilate a broad (constantly evolving) and sufficiently deep understanding of our technical products and systems&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to quickly understand our products and stay current on the evolution of our business strategy&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience navigating business structures while maintaining confidentiality and discretion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to capture complex concepts quickly and communicate them succinctly to key stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to handle shifting priorities while maintaining organization and control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading cross-functional projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiar with the GTM roadmap for large business areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internalize the best ideas from large organizations while also setting a vision that others are excited to get behind&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in a sales or GTM role is preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

